    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I can empathize with the stories of the men who have gone through the ordeal of prostate cancer (''More Options, and Decisions, for Men With Prostate Cancer,'' Oct. 3). I admire the honesty and courage of those who told their stories; it is not an easy thing to do.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I can empathize with the stories of the men who have gone through the ordeal of prostate cancer (''More Options, and Decisions, for Men With Prostate Cancer,'' Oct. 3). I admire the honesty and courage of those who told their stories; it is not an easy thing to do.</p>
        <p>I had my prostate removed almost 11 years ago, at 59, and have suffered the debilitating effects ever since, but, such as it is, I am still alive.</p>
        <p>WALTER J. MURRAY  St. Paul</p>
      </block>
